"text": "More tips:

"text": "Juniors 🤘

"text": "Happy New Year from all of us at Supergiant!!\ud83c\udf86\ud83c\udf8a\ud83c\udfa3 Thank you for an unforgettable year gone by, and may the Fates grant good RNG in 2021.\n\nTo mark the occasion, please enjoy some chthonic gods effortlessly navigating through Chaos, courtesy of @0jenzee0. #HadesGame #HappyNewYear https://t.co/HJ8Mrr4pZ6",
"text": "I refuse to be excited for another year",
"text": "Grabbing a coffee for some cozy Genshin to wrap up the year with y\u2019all. Live shortly",

"text": "#NoWords-Seeing fan's reactions to Luke's return is something I will cherish forever. Their anticipation seeing the X-Wing/Ep. 6 Robes/a lightsaber/a GREEN lightsaber/a gloved hand/an ungloved hand/a Force choke/R2-was OVERWHELMING & very moving to me-1/2  https://t.co/gzKn9IVPf6",
"text": "I've been a part of making many big games, but they didn't make me as proud as the simple asteroids clone I made with my son during the break. #unity3d",
"text": "My goals for next year? Just fucking crack on with it and get shit done \ud83d\ude02.\n\nHave a good en mates! https://t.co/TBqmWlggJC",
"text": "Happy new year guys. Thanks for being there for me this year and hopefully for the next one, I appreciate you all.\n\nMay all your dreams for 2021 come true \ud83d\udc4d",
"text": "Silence your quarry with this scaly Somnacanth set of equipment. #MHRise https://t.co/iXSJNYxzSL",
"text": "um excuse every single one of you for not once telling me how lit Astro\u2019s Playroom is",

"text": "And I *do* celebrate all things — and more.

But that celebration sits next to deep, deep grief.

— and recognition of the heavy lifting, the  labors of love that still lie ahead.",

"text": "I want to celebrate today. 

I want to celebrate the inauguration of the nation’s first Black and South Asian woman as Vice President. 

I want to celebrate the inauguration of a President who worked as a partner and ally to our nation’s first Black president.",

"text": "Every time I see someone say we “survived” the last four years, I think about all who did not survive to see this day.

More than 400K Covid-related deaths.

More Black, brown, and Indigenous lives taken too soon, including those who, in the last week, were killed on death row.",

"text": "On this inauguration morning, some thoughts I’ve been having the last few days:

I don’t know what the word is, but I do wish I could feel happy about today. 

Yes, it represents turning point. Yes, it is a historic day. And yes, it is most awaited and welcomed. 

And yet...",

"text": "Amanda Gorman was just sensational. What a talent.",

"text": "For those of us who don't exactly have a positive image of the US, this just looks like a giant dystopian cult setting.\n\nIf you want to get an idea of the perspective I see this from, look at the grand Nazi rallies that took place both in the US and Germany in the past.",
"text": "So, our poet laureate is absolutely gorgeous as well as a beautiful poet.",
"text": "\"even as we tired we tried\" -- Amanda Gorman",
"text": "\u201cBut while democracy can be periodically delayed,\nIt can never be permanently defeated.\u201d\n@TheAmandaGorman",

"text": "Fashion/aesthetics/optics definitely do serve a role. It can serve a distracting role, to get you to have a positive image of the same persons who are responsible for the worst acts of violence around the world.",

"text": "The Obama administration committed awful atrocities and persons still say that his biggest scandal was wearing a tan suit.\n\nHis charisma allowed him to dodge criticism when many of the things that you associated with Trump had been done during his administration.",
"text": "But since more clarity has been demanded, here: https://t.co/tlLn0HqWpx",
"text": "Initially, I didn't intend to make a thread. I make too many threads. https://t.co/d9hoLh2OYM",

"text": "It's the same thing when crediting the most awful persons for being 'intelligent' - yeah they're intelligent but what function do they serve? Why do you care that they're intelligent? Why just admire anyone with power while disregarding the specific things they use power to do?",

"text": "That's another limitation of caring exclusively about optics: you can immediately remember that something is important or significant but you don't think about why they are important or what function they serve. All that matters if that they're important.",

"text": "What I said shouldn't been interpreted as \"don't care about optics or fashion\" or \"optics and fashion are not important\" - aesthetics are very important. Symbolism is important.\n\nBut why are they important? What function do they serve? https://t.co/i3Ew1SNWic",

"text": "I said that some persons care *more* about A *than* they do about B. That is not saying persons shouldn't care about A.\n\nI said that politics is *just* about optics for a lot of persons. That is not saying that politics should totally disregard optics.",

"text": "I typed out entire sentences, and all some of you read was:

- "Some of you care about optics"

"text": "5 minutes late already. So good to greet everyone. \n\nIt's time to share. Feel free to take a snapshot of your text if necessary. Then take a look at how others handle this out of sequence information.  #linebylinetime",
"text": "@SilverAbby84 @graestonewriter This is my first time editing a full novel. I'm going by the method I use for short stories. It works well, but I'm willing to learn other ways too.",
"text": "@RebeccaJAmiss @graestonewriter I hear that. Looking at my work as a whole, I know where I can cut better than when I was in the thick of writing it. So, good point there.",

"text": "@SilverAbby84 @graestonewriter I'm struggling a bit with that right now lol. There are some things I know has to be cut, but others I'm waiting until revisions to read it back to see how it flows as I put the edits in.",

"text": "@LeChatGris3 @graestonewriter It's an art for sure! Good to see you, CD!",
"text": "@LeChatGris3 Welcome, CD. Not dumping is the technical term, I believe! Ha. They even call the local \"dump\" a sanitary landfill. I don't know what's sanitary, but anyway...",

"text": "@DelightfullyThe @graestonewriter @SilverAbby84 Hello, Harlow. I'm on time and equally unprepared.\n\n#LineByLineTime",
"text": "@Elderac Hello, Mark. I love your personal backstory.",
"text": "@graestonewriter Hello Everyone. It's Ernie, who writes MG/YA fantasy. I've had characters tell their story that takes up a chapter.\n\n#LineByLineTime",

"text": "@graestonewriter Hi, I'm Rebecca. I write historical and contemporary fiction. I like using dialogue to introduce or provide backstory. I think it works peppered throughout. #LineByLineTime",

"text": "@graestonewriter Hello #LineByLineTime amigos! I'm Abigail, slinger of #SFF sludge.\n\nI build such large worlds that backstory is sort of inevitable. My usual attempt at making it interesting is through dialogue. And how much is needed? Usually enough to understand the story and not a letter more.",

"text": "@graestonewriter Hola writer friends. Mackenzie here, writer of women's fiction and short stories. Backstory gives a current situation context. There's no real maximum I guess, but it should be woven seamlessly into the narrative or dialogue, otherwise it's choppy.",

"text": "#LineByLineTime\nWelcome, #Writer friends. Gather \u2018round the table. Introduce yourself and your writing. When is \"backstory\" a good idea? What is the maximum length for backstory? https://t.co/7hOJaBDz6U",

"text": "Personally, I find the quickest way of making a TTRPG inaccessible is to use custom dice.\n\nYes, they may make the game play more smoothly, but as soon as I need the players to buy special (expensive) sets to play, especially if we may only play once or twice, interest disappears",

"text": "ADHD is real. Executive dysfunction is real. These little obstacles that build up and ruin your day are real. You're not lazy, you're not making excuses. And you can reshape the world around you in a way that let's you do the things that you love.",

"text": "Dollie + Cookie Diner Pouches\ud83c\udf66Drop FRIDAY @ 12 PM (Noon) ET \ud83c\udf54 Link in Replies!\n\nI have a limited quantity, so I set a time out of caution~ They will be listed + priced individually to account for imperfections since I am still learning to print successfully at home! \ud83d\ude33\ud83d\udca6 https://t.co/rgg68lqsYp",
"text": "long girls with long hair \u2764\ufe0f\n\n(Jae is mine, Chaewon belongs to @/tinyangryghost) https://t.co/lEblnfX5hV",

"text": "Well I'm here to tell you that you don't have to be ashamed of it. It happens to me, it happens to everyone. If you feel seen by this thread, you're a real artist and you deserve the space and comfort to make your art how you want to.",

"text": "I think we all feel some shame when we notice that such small, seemingly insignificant obstacles completely block our creativity. How can I be a \"real\" artist if something as simple as, say, a messy room completely kills my creativity?",
"text": "Remember when people used to say homosexuality was a \"phase\"? I still laugh about it. Longest phase of my life, tbh. When will it end? \ud83d\ude2d\ud83d\ude2d\ud83d\ude2d",

"text": "One of the uncomfortable truths of the world is that many, many of the great artists we admire had lives of privilege and comfort, or had lots of help from others who remain uncredited. They often just had fewer obstacles than most of us. So why should you suffer unnecessarily?",

"text": "\ud83e\udd70\ud83d\udc0e\u2600\ufe0f\ud83c\udf3b\n\u201cqt with a photo of you that somebody else has taken. selfies are not allowed. it can be old or new but ideally one that really captures you.\u201d https://t.co/bqYQqykFbW https://t.co/y0x1Dk9Mvw",

"text": "This is why I never cared for the mindset that great art only comes from severe limitation. There's nothing wrong with wanting to spend the money to get better tools for your work, or devoting extra effort to make yourself comfortable while you work.",
"text": "every time one of my friends who draw horror art post a very creepy creature drawing my brain goes \u201cthat\u2019s my friend :3\u201d at the thing",

"text": "A significant part of your creative life will be devoted to removing as many of those obstacles as possible. Setting up a dedicated space for your work, that's always available and has no other purpose, makes a huge difference, for example.",

"text": "For a creative with ADHD, even the smallest obstacle between you and your work can completely derail your plans for the day. Did you put aside your midi keyboard yesterday? There's a good chance you'll decide setting it up isn't worth it and you'll put off your work til tomorrow.",
"text": "I DID IT (FOR SURE THIS TIME). \ud83d\udc69\ud83c\udffb\u200d\ud83c\udf93 https://t.co/GitScY0iBp",

"text": "i have an *extremely* difficult time turning off work brain. my brain is constantly working. 2 decades of working in beds, busses, libraries, couches, tables, cars... no place is \u201csafe\u201d from work for me. it\u2019s a... concerning habit.",

"text": "i am a perfectionist and a workaholic... both things i think are negative, and only ever really see in a negative light. i only ever feel like i\u2019m wasting every moment, but sometimes i see myself through other people\u2019s eyes at just how... frighteningly obsessive i am. it\u2019s weird",

"text": "Cis people have no idea how easy it is for trans women to tell the difference between someone who sees them as a women and someone who sees them as a man that they have to remember to refer to as a woman.",

"text": "i don’t usually post photos of myself, but my partner has a series of photos of me working on ikenfell in... various places.
- in a car

"text": "You know, my to-do list doesn\u2019t seem so stressful when you compare it to this one. https://t.co/gWKEFl6MqQ",
"text": "The Mandalorian Chapter 10: The Passenger https://t.co/5Qw9UYALvw",
"text": "I couldn\u2019t place what I\u2019ve been feeling all day until now, and that is HOPE. \u2665\ufe0f",

"text": "Let us breathe. 
Let us pray. 
Let us hope. 
Let us mourn. 
Let us dream. 
And let’s get to work for an America that is as worthy, noble, empathetic, and inclusive as its founding ideals.",

"text": "After taking the oath of office this afternoon, I got right to work taking action to:

- Control the pandemic
- Provide economic relief
- Tackle climate change
- Advance racial equity",
"text": "She asked every 5 mins throughout the entire ceremony if she could meet @HillaryClinton https://t.co/pQIRAM7mvP",
"text": "I am once again asking you to check out these memes. https://t.co/1jMQkyTCNZ",

"text": "Today, two people with speech impediments addressed the nation (and world), and they did so eloquently and confidently. As someone sometimes terrified to speak publicly because of the \"good-natured\" teasing I still get, this was inspiring in a special kind of way.",

"text": "I see some people on Twitter are thanking me for helping guide them through the last 4 years. I am humbled and deeply appreciative. I also don\u2019t plan on going anywhere quite yet. \ud83d\ude00 In fact, I have what I hope will be an exciting announcement on a new initiative coming soon.",
"text": "It\u2019s official: Democrats have a majority in the United States Senate. Welcome @ReverendWarnock, @Ossoff, @AlexPadilla4CA. Now let\u2019s get to work.",

"text": "For all the pomp and ceremony, for all of this being about Joe Biden\u2019s inauguration for president, a job he has wanted for decades, the ceremony was broad, diverse, and beautiful. It was so much bigger than being about just one man... How refreshing.",

"text": "On a day for the history books, @TheAmandaGorman delivered a poem that more than met the moment. Young people like her are proof that \"there is always light, if only we're brave enough to see it; if only we're brave enough to be it.\" https://t.co/mbywtvjtEH",

"text": "Join us next week for our #ACESchat with @JazzAuthor! Debbie Burke is an award-winner editor, ghostwriter, and author. Join us as we dive into the editor/author relationship. Debbie will discuss tips for editors working with new authors and even going from author to editor. https://t.co/cwKHO7qvIJ",
"text": "\u26a1\ud83d\udc09 Mega Ampharos is appearing in Mega Raids in areas around the world! \u26a1\ud83d\udc09  Are you ready to take on this Electric- and Dragon-type Pok\u00e9mon?",
"text": "Did someone say...Madame Vice President?!?!? https://t.co/T2ULqxF7L9",
"text": "Hands up, who else cried?",
"text": "Wasn't @TheAmandaGorman\u2019s poem just stunning? She's promised to run for president in 2036 and I for one can't wait. https://t.co/rahEClc6k2",

"text": "Honored to witness history today. May God bless @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris as they take on the work of healing our nation. May we all fulfill our duty as citizens to help our country and our fellow Americans through the challenges ahead. https://t.co/dooSLnFePe",
"text": "\"I ran a spellcheck, so it should be good to go.\"\ncopy editor: https://t.co/0fHO2ZJGDi",

"text": "@TheAmandaGorman @HamiltonMusical You were perfect. Perfectly written, perfectly delivered. Every bit of it. Brava! -LMM",

"text": "My favorite line from the poem by @TheAmandaGorman today: \u201cWe lift our gazes not to what stands between us but what stands before us.\u201d She is amazing. #inauguration2021 https://t.co/OgFRkOn7e1",

"text": "Inaugural poet Amanda Gorman summoned images dire and triumphant as she called out to the world \u201ceven as we grieved, we grew.\u201d The country\u2019s first National Youth Poet Laureate, Gorman, 22, is by far the youngest poet for a presidential #Inauguration. https://t.co/BBzcmuEsTl",
"text": "Never underestimate the ability to heal.",
"text": "Thx @Lin_Manuel ! Did you catch the 2 @HamiltonMusical references in the inaugural poem? I couldn\u2019t help myself! https://t.co/22UTKkGTLq",
"text": "Did you hear that? I think I heard Lady Liberty letting out a giant sigh of relief.",
"text": "Goosebumps and happy tears. Congratulations @POTUS  and @VP on this momentous occasion for our Democracy.",

"text": "Friends, it is ok to celebrate and find joy, knowing the work MUST begin (again) soon after.\n\nThe work will always be there, in new manifestations. Take these opportunities for happiness as they come, and now we prepare to dig in. #LetsGetLoud",
"text": "This poem was such an incredible way to celebrate and acknowledge where America is in this moment. Absolutely breathtaking. https://t.co/SyMgyrxWRs",
"text": "full video of @TheAmandaGorman\u2019s poem today https://t.co/sEy9hBg9Z9",
"text": "Full video: Inaugural poet Amanda Gorman https://t.co/1FF4dfia9h",

"text": "\"Being American is more than a pride we inherit. It's the past we step into.\" \n\nAmanda Gorman, the first National Youth Poet Laureate, reads a poem during Joe Biden's inaugural address  https://t.co/EJnm38Ii1A https://t.co/OurIhLRFek",

"text": "Backstory: Amanda Gorman had been struggling to write that poem. Then came the assault on the Capitol. That night she stayed up late and finished, certain of what she wanted to say. https://t.co/usNEYuPMmO",
"text": "THIS. This is who are are.\n\n\u201cFor there is always light if only we are brave enough to see it, if only we are brave enough to be it.\u201d -@TheAmandaGorman",

"text": "“We lift our gazes not to what stands between us but what stands before us.” 

Oh, @TheAmandaGorman - you and your words are the balm we need right now. 
Thank you.",

"text": "The most thrilling part of #InaugurationDay2021 -watching inaugural youth poet laureate, Amanda Gorman, preach her dreams to @JoeBiden @KamalaHarris & all of us. \"If we merge mercy with might, and might with right... we will rebuild, reconcile, and recover... the new dawn blooms\" https://t.co/T4WNcUKTHv",
"text": "This visual, of Vice President Harris sitting in state in her special chair, with her spouse sitting proudly behind her... is kind of EVERYTHING to me. https://t.co/vbB9PZNAG6",
"text": "\u201cWe realize that quiet isn\u2019t always peace.\u201d @TheAmandaGorman #Inauguration",
"text": "today\u2019s biggest takeaway is that Twitter now has two more perfect Bernie meme frames https://t.co/9yPzm7ADIs",
"text": "I think the whole world just exhaled.",
"text": "Bernie's commitment to being perma-pissed until everyone has medicare for all is outstanding. Those mittens are all business. https://t.co/FgUkeHxvyq",
"text": "Oh right, that\u2019s what a president is supposed to sound like.",
"text": "A man who overcame a stutter, gives a stirring inaugural addresses. A man whose life has been torn by tragedy, summons hope. Anything is possible.",
"text": "\"We must reject the culture in which facts themselves are manipulated and even manufactured.\"\n\u2014 President Joe Biden",
"text": "Big day for complete sentences.",
"text": "America, say it with me: President Joe Biden.",
"text": "My cat when JLo broke into \u201cLet\u2019s get Loud\u201d \ud83d\ude02 https://t.co/HemrhcnFGU",
"text": "Time to cut the -elect! From now on, it's President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris.\n\n(And we lowercase former president Donald Trump.)",
"text": "\u201clet\u2019s get loud\u201d by Jlo was played at every Hillary Clinton rally in 2016 \ud83d\ude36",
"text": "#CopyeditingProTip\n\nMadam Vice President",

"text": ".@KamalaHarris, the first African American, Asian American, and woman to become Vice President, is sworn in by Justice Sonia Sotomayor, the first Latina on the Supreme Court. This is what breaking the glass ceiling looks like.",

"text": "I am by no means a patriotic person, but seeing the pledge of allegiance signed in ASL by the person also speaking it, and not just by an interpreter... that sent a signal from the Biden Administration.",
"text": "The swearing in of Kamala Harris by Justice Sotomayor. Wow. America has a new vision of what is possible.",
"text": "I should have not worn mascara today.",
"text": "HERstory \ud83d\udda4 https://t.co/IwqJj564Aq",
"text": "What an absolutely remarkable photo. https://t.co/Yae9m8w47S",
"text": "Inside the envelope is an article Bernie cut out of the newspaper that he thought Biden would find interesting https://t.co/E2t7kYiPMN",
"text": "Michelle Obama\u2019s hair is really laid like a bridge over troubled waters. #InaugurationDay https://t.co/rgAFiSO4Bq",
"text": "Klobuchar\u2019s speech is a gem. Beautiful. Evocative.",

"text": "Today will be the fourth time Chief Justice John Roberts has sworn in a U.S. president \u2013 and the third time the man standing across from him was someone who voted against his nomination to the highest court. #Inauguration https://t.co/gbRCCrnWSI",
"text": "It falls to all of us, not just the two leaders we are inaugurating today, to take up the torch of our democracy, not as a weapon of political arson, but as an instrument for good.",
"text": "This is the day our democracy picks itself up, brushes off the dust, and does what America always does: goes forward as a nation, under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all.",
"text": "What a great and historic day!! https://t.co/ewHzQ5pZoc",
"text": "The pose. The mittens. The social distance. https://t.co/kwHH7AzZY8",

"text": "To stress - the line between creator and audience member is not there to preserve some kind of hierarchy or status. It is there to protect the safety and comfort of BOTH parties. That is why boundaries are so important.",

"text": "But it crosses the very important line between content creator and audience member that so often gets blurred. Both myself and a follower may publicly thirst over my partner, but that doesn\u2019t give us something to bond over and it shouldn\u2019t blur that line.",

"text": "This behaviour is seen frequently with friendship groups too. If you\u2019re a content creator with a online friendship group you interact with, you\u2019ll always have strangers trying to insert themselves into that dynamic as a way to feel closer to you. It comes with the territory.",

"text": "I get it. I thirst over my partner every second of the damn day. I thirst over them with my friends. And yes - I also thirst over them publicly, on the internet. But that isn\u2019t an invitation for strangers to insert themselves into my relationship dynamic.",

"text": "I\u2019m not annoyed that people are thirsting over my partner (I mean, have you SEEN them?) But when a stranger directly tags me in a thirst comment, they are using my relationship with my partner to position themselves closer to TT, or relate to me, which crosses several boundaries.",

"text": "Getting into 2021 nd realizing I've been watching @nyxrising since 2016- so many memories are attached to the videos I've watched, its definitely a hell of a trip down memory lane, but I'm so glad I found them because I made it through so much because of them. I love these dorks.",

"text": "We have literal kids feeling abnormal/wrong for not being hypersexual, or not fulfilling the expected paradigms of a label. Particularly among queer influencers, entire personalities and content are centred around being a top/bottom/switch and it isolates a huge number of people.",

"text": "People discuss sex and sexual preferences far more openly nowadays, and it is good to normalise these things but it does uphold a dangerous social standard of hypersexualisation which is often veiled as being \u201csex positive\u201d. These aren\u2019t the same things.",

"text": "I feel like lately young, impressionable people are being exposed to certain sexual acts and dynamics without any of the crucial education around consent and safety. The aggressive categorisation of queer people into binaries such as top/bottom is also very damaging.",

"text": "It stresses me out at how normalised extreme sexual dynamics are on TikTok, especially with young, queer people. All sexual and non-sexual experiences are valid but please don\u2019t think you are \u201cboring\u201d or \u201cvanilla\u201d if you don\u2019t like being choked.",

"text": "Black Hollywood is small. Like a small village. When you think about it, there\u2019s really a handful of us working actors, writers, HODs, crew, directors in a massive industry. "text": "Only Chadwick could embody Jackie Robinson, Thurgood Marshall, and T\u2019Challa. He, too, knew what it meant to persevere. To summon real strength. And he\u00a0belongs right there with them as a hero\u2014for Black kids and for all our kids. There\u2019s no better gift to give our world.\u00a0\u2764 https://t.co/t2tjZDMxNT",

"text": "pronouncing bon iver like bon eye-ver in front of indie guys just to feel something",
"text": "Rest in Power Chadwick Boseman. \ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udffe https://t.co/ZgyWG8FXAp",
"text": "the best way for me to express my pain and sorrow is through creating.\n\nthis is for you, chadwick. \ud83d\udd4a\ufe0f https://t.co/9K00RLUySm",

"text": "Artists bring us experiences and invite us into their worlds of expression.

"text": "I want to be crystal clear: without Chadwick, and what he gave to his character, there is no Shang Chi. Period. My  career rides on the coattails of a great man. \n\nI wish I would have had the opportunity to tell him in person - but I'll fight for him always, my Eternal King.",

"text": "Rest now. In power and peace. https://t.co/YSPh6QUlmz",

"text": "Not even amidst pervasive grieving do the reactionary, and often spite-driven, takes pause.",

"text": "Our makeup artists are friends and he used to get on the phone and ask me to sing \u201cYou Mean The World To Me\u201d because it was his favorite song of mine and now this song will be forever dedicated to him. Rest In Power King. https://t.co/SnSn1UdhUB",
"text": "Sending so much love to his family \ud83d\udc94Grateful for the light he brought in to the world and heartbroken by his loss https://t.co/X5yPaE3A0g",

"text": "Allow people to commemorate and grieve and process and reflect in whatever way brings them catharsis. \n\nThere's no need to throw a critical lens on grief. I know virtue-nitpicking drives a lot of people's content---but it's been one hour.",
"text": "Thank you for everything. Rest in Power, Chadwick Boseman. \ud83d\ude4f\ud83c\udffe https://t.co/suxz2VhiIK",
"text": "Our hearts are broken and our thoughts are with Chadwick Boseman\u2019s family. Your legacy will live on forever. Rest In Peace. https://t.co/GduiuaXufw",

"text": "We are all heartbroken by the tragic loss of #chadwickboseman -- an extraordinary talent, and one of the most gentle and giving souls I have ever met.  He brought enormous strength, dignity and depth to his groundbreaking role of Black Panther; shattering myths and stereotypes,",

"text": "Chadwick.....no words to express my devastation of losing you. Your talent, your spirit, your heart, your authenticity........It was an honor working beside you, getting to know you....Rest well prince...May flights of angels sing thee to thy heavenly rest. I love you! \ud83d\udc9b\ud83d\udc9b\ud83d\udc9b https://t.co/6abglPBOsh",

"text": "I\u2019m absolutely devastated. This is beyond heartbreaking. \n\nChadwick was special. A true original. He was a deeply committed and constantly curious artist. He had so much amazing work still left to create. I\u2019m endlessly grateful for our friendship. Rest in power, King\ud83d\udc99 https://t.co/oBERXlw66Z",
"text": "May you have a beautiful return, King. We will miss you so. https://t.co/jdip3RHoXb",
"text": "Our hearts are broken and our thoughts are with Chadwick Boseman's family. Your legacy will live on forever. Rest In Peace. https://t.co/QNvzuZgAbe",
"text": "\ud83d\udc94 https://t.co/Y8ZbFdpHCe",

"text": "God of our silent tears! A brillant & talented actor, gone to soon. @chadwickboseman you leave this earth w/a beautiful body of work. When you graced our screens you brought the dignity & grace we could all be proud of.  My prayers are with your loving family. RIP my dear son CTD",
"text": "A warrior of light til the very end. A true king. I am without words. May he rise in power. https://t.co/50nfbvZpAq",

"text": "I keep thinking about my 3-year-old in his Black Panther costume. How he wore it almost every day when he got it, refused to take it off. The way he walked around saying \u201cI\u2019m the Black Panther.\u201d How happy it made him. What Chadwick gave us was immeasurable. What an enormous loss.",

"text": "Chadwick was diagnosed with colon cancer four years ago, per reports. During that time, he gave us Civil War, Marshall, Black Panther, Infinity War, Endgame, 21 Bridges and Da 5 Bloods. Lord only knows what he was going through on a daily basis.",
"text": "Chadwick Boseman was a hero to me. Seeing him rise out of SC and become so successful, bc of him I knew I would be able to as well. Such an inspiration. RIP. \ud83d\udd4a",
"text": "In power \n\nEternally in power",

"text": "So I\u2019ve been banned from @Facebook for the first time in my life since I started my account in 2007 for 24 hours. For sharing someone else\u2019s view on hydroxychloroquine. I have a very clear and direct message to Facebook a brand without trust that does not allow debate will die.",

"text": "This is me aged 5 with my 10mth younger brother. It wasn't just the #CSA that messed our heads up it was that for as long as we could remember he'd used drugs & alcohol to make us pliable. "text": "@Aimee_B22x You have a heart of gold, you miss them but they would hurt you again

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Exactly. The hate should be directed at the abuser, not the abused. We really do live in a society with a bass-awkward mentality.",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x 4\nI can send love your way and offer warm gentle huggs from my thoughts to you in words via the internet...or offer a space to listen.  \nGOOD LUCK X",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x 3\nStay in the now as much as you can  reach out to those who understand and those whom accept and allow you supportive safe spaces to be. Most of all remember ..OTHERS HEAR YOU and FEEL YOU and you MATTER.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x 2\nthey could climb inside you and feel your pain ...I just wanted to feel love and validated and safe when I spoke out BUT I was outcast, avoided and ties where severed.  It can be difficult for others to understand Aimee as the pain you have been subject to is very personal.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x 1\nYes it does seem this way ..... for what it is worth ..when I feel these thoughts consume me. I try to gently bring my thoughts to the reasons I spoke up and remember I take the power back \" If only others really knew how difficult it is for you ...its like sometimes you wish",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x I speak from experience that I only found some start to recovery when I talked to others about what had been done to me x",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x Just remember the strength it took. Always here\u2764\ufe0f",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x But if you didn't speak out and speak up, the pain of concealing it would eventually have destroyed you mentally. You've done the right thing. Find new people who truly love you x",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Am signing off shortly, for tonight, but just so you know: CBT is limited in what it can help with. It isn't you that has issues too complex, it is the CBT that is too limited. \nTake care.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x That's completely natural. It's like waves in the ocean. They will lessen in time. \u2764 You've got this.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x I'm proud of you\u2764\ud83d\udcaa It takes strength and courage. I'm so sorry you are hurting now as a result of it but know those who left were not worthy of who you are. You are on your healing path. Sending you lotsa love from here\u2764",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x There are people you have yet to meet who will give you the love and support you need and deserce just as you are - strong and brave, not frightened to speak. If, in due course, some of the friends and family you have lost can learn and grow, they may join you in your new life.",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x You're in the UK?",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Its abhorrent behaviour and inexcusable. Their weaknesses are not something we have to accept but acknowledge&lay the responsibility at their shoulders not ours. Easier said than done I know \ud83d\udc9c but I also know a victim isn\u2019t to blame for speaking to truth.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x I don\u2019t know you but I hear you as I\u2019ve been through something similar, speaking out was essential. Not everyone will stick around but you need to accept that is ok. Those who do are genuinely looking out for you. Be kind to yourself, you are worth everything, hope you\u2019re ok x",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x I don't know you and can't begin to imagine how you're feeling but my heart is breaking that you had to experience that and lose the people who should be supporting you. They don't deserve you. Don't try to go back; move forward, find new friends and live the life you deserve. \ud83d\udc95",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x Glad to hear that.",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x Are you in physical danger?",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x @ElliottVictoria Of course it is when they should be standing by you and applauding your courage.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x What? Really? No professional therapist would turn down a client for being complex. Everyone is complex - just most don't realise it yet as live in denial of their true selves.\nDM me if you want to chat. Take care either way.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x You did the right thing. And just remember you're not alone. I'm here if you ever need event. I totally get it.",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x Anyone who walked away from you for sharing your abuse is not a real friend, or ignorant or both. You don't need people like that. How are you now?",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x @dyslexiadilema @RespectYourself Thats amazing. I'm glad you have someone. I cant imagine how much courage it must have taken for you to go through what you have. You are a warrior.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Please, you did the right thing in talking about your abuse. You are very brave. It saddens me that you've had negative reactions from those who should be supportive. It might be that it's too painful for some of them to cope with. You matter; never forget this. I'll follow you.",

"text": "This is something we all face. I am now NC with my adoptive family, in its entirety. We can stand up and stand strong in knowing we did the right thing. You are an amazing woman, a survivor, and are thriving as you move forward, @Aimee_B22x https://t.co/63FexuboVD",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x @RespectYourself You did the right thing. It may not seem that way right now, but time will show you true benefits.",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x You're incredible, Aimee. I know you'd give anything to spend more time with those people but the fact you can't in entirely the fault of your abuser. That abuse is never on you, not ever. You're an incredible woman \u2764\ufe0f\u2764\ufe0f",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x Sorry for the typos there!",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Hey lovely So sorry you lost friends n family because you spike out. That is not your fault. And being abused is not your fault. "text": "@Aimee_B22x So sorry - and this is one reason that abusers get away with it - because the fallout for their victims is so huge.",
"text": "@Aimee_B22x @RespectYourself Hugs. I so, so admire you for going public. So sorry your friends did not understand that you had to do it",

"text": "@Aimee_B22x Also, a lot of times people may not believe you initially, and you may lose them, only for them to return to you and say \"YOU WERE RIGHT! Please forgive me.\"  I'm sorry, Aimee. I'm going through a lot of this, too. \ud83c\udf38",

"text": "The woman cleaning The White House this morning https://t.co/7JR2IFxV5g",
"text": "Trump at departure ceremony: \u201cWe were not a regular administration.\u201d",
"text": "Shameful. So relieved for America and the free world that they have rid themselves of this moron.",

"text": "He is finally gone. The nightmare has come to its fitful end. A bunch of trump elite criminals pardoned in the shroud of night. The Golden Toilet Presidency is over. A turd is a turd no matter where it lays.",
"text": "What a petulant, destructive toddler.",
"text": "@Kerri_Lauren It\u2019s party time! \ud83e\udd73\ud83e\udd73\ud83e\udd73 #InaugurationDay",
"text": "Quality tweet is quality: https://t.co/H44HnJQQKe",
"text": "A bitter and disgraced Trump exited the White House for the last time as the 45th president of the US. https://t.co/FPLfH0HD29",

"text": "\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8 https://t.co/u6lt5nt5vr",
"text": "Happy day to you and all my lovely American friends. \ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83d\udc9a\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83d\udc9a\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83d\udc9a https://t.co/mc9fxap1eY",
"text": "I hadn\u2019t cried yet today until I read this. \ud83d\ude4c\ud83c\udffe\ud83d\ude4c\ud83c\udffe\ud83d\ude4c\ud83c\udffe https://t.co/pVjbgBVipC",

"text": "Dropped my daughter off at school and before she got out of the car I told her when I picked her up there will be a Black woman as Vice President. Her face lit up like sunshine. Amid all the craziness, been little time to acknowledge and savor that. But what a day.",
"text": "https://t.co/420qd0pura",
"text": "BYE.",
"text": "Woke up at 4am like a kid on Christmas morning. #InaugurationDay",
"text": "Still here, never left. https://t.co/VtvUS95MDa",
"text": "https://t.co/QvtDDWl6Q0",
"text": "Joe Biden is the first actor from Parks and Recreation to become the President of the United States.",
"text": "White House security waking the Trump family up tomorrow: https://t.co/zaWNUBhc07",
"text": "Oh no, he pardoned Steve Bannon, who definitely never committed a state crime!",
"text": "It has come to my attention that this tweet did not achieve its original intention which was, of course, to UNIFY. \ud83d\udc99 https://t.co/RAXUAO4o5V",
"text": "It was exactly as bad as we said it would be. Good riddance. \n\nDon\u2019t dare show your fucking face in NYC ever again.",
"text": "I just finished #TedLasso, and my only complaint is that we never learn what a British owl says.",

"text": "Tonight, in Washington, D.C. and across the nation, we came together to honor the over 400,000 Americans we\u2019ve lost to COVID-19. The last year has tested us in unimaginable ways, but now it\u2019s time we begin to heal and overcome \u2014 together. https://t.co/DuWhN1xjNO",

"text": "At Fox, it\u2019s forever 2016. \nTomorrow, here in 2021, @JoeBiden & @KamalaHarris will be sworn in as our next President and Vice President. My mom @HillaryClinton will be there. \n\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8 https://t.co/mg4VpGSrOo",
"text": "https://t.co/kCjndh0qyh",
"text": "Though we may be physically separated, we, the American people are united in spirit. https://t.co/s5v4KIjbSX",
"text": "Final schedule for Trump... https://t.co/UfhPJolTKi",
"text": "Still can\u2019t get over the fact that tonight Washington DC is on lockdown to protect Washington DC from The President of the United States.",

"text": "This. The view from my roof deck. For those that left. For those that are worried. For those that think  we are dead... the heart of New York City is still beating. It never stopped and it never will. https://t.co/z38SxRGsNG",
"text": "@Acosta Weird choice not to water the lawn. \n\nWould not have expected that of Trump.",
"text": "Good night from the Washington Monument, looking down at our gorgeous National Mall, ready for #Inauguration2021 #WashingtonDC https://t.co/HqoeaIwcmN",
"text": "Tomorrow. https://t.co/DtWBChEdQv",
"text": "Listen... The Academy... I just want to TALK https://t.co/SbTeFxPhYS",
"text": "Tonight feels like Christmas Eve and Armageddon Eve combined.",
"text": "First look at Patronus Minerva McGonagall and Lupin! https://t.co/F3W3BxDr7E",
"text": "Well it was more or less exactly as horrible as we imagined.",
"text": "Becoming. https://t.co/h8TGMBy7RI",

"text": "So, yeah. Been picking myself up and moving forward. Hoping for next year to be a better one\u2014 i will MAKE it be a better one. Thanks for reading. Let's all hope and work for a kinder future. :) \ud83d\udc95",

"text": "anyway since then I\u2019ve been learning what adult life is like single. I will never be \"over\" the way I was (and am) treated, & things are rough, but i AM doing all right. i picked up a lot of new hobbies & im learning to be happy as I am. I'm just gonna be a spinster stereotype.",

"text": "It would be tough on its own, but in the isolating year of 2020 that was an extra layer of Lemley Is Gonna Get Character Development lmao. i coped by doing a lot of crosswords. like... a lot of crosswords. so many crosswords. did u know they use the word \u201cErie\u201d a lot? LOL",

"text": "I\u2019m not aggrieved over being broken up with per se- i'm a strong believer in a person's apology and amends saying more about them than their mistake. But neither person involved wants to admit to it, let alone reconcile damage, so I\u2019ve had to try and bandage the wound by myself.",

"text": "You can imagine what that did to my self esteem LMAO. i won\u2019t go into detail but i got MAD fucked up. My life trajectory crumbled overnight-- the future i'd been planning for years went up in smoke, and i wasn't given the dignity of knowing there was a problem in the first place.",

"text": "TLDR my fiancee fell out of love with me but had an emotional affair with another friend instead of communicating with me. When that friend(who was also dating another person) confessed to her, my fiancee dumped me the next day in hopes of pursuing her.",
"text": "and i'm sure some people were wondering wtf happened to the wife I suddenly stopped mentioning this summer, haha.",

"text": "re: that last one, I didn\u2019t say anything When it happened bc I didn't want to look like I was retaliating, but I also don't wanna Not Talk about something that deeply affected me and changed my life, yknow? so yeah, end of the year seemed like a good time to reminisce.",

"text": "[cw: severe end of yr navelgazing thread lol]\nMan... 2020 has been rough, inside and out. Reflecting personally, all kind of shit happened\u2014 cat illness, family death, and my fiancee/partner of seven yrs left me for another girl. ive changed A Lot!",

"text": "I know agents say this EVERY YEAR but perhaps I can be the first in 2020 to please ask:
Dear #NaNoWriMo participants,

"text": "Can't believe it needs to be said AGAIN, don't respond to agent passes by commenting on their  romantic life/interests. Even if it is \"you're so nice! You must have a ton of bfs\" or \"men must be lining up for you\". \n\nIt's not cute. It's disturbing #querytip #amquerying",

"text": "and to tell someone \"no, don't take that offer from a reputable mid-sized press!\" is purposefully sabotaging someone.\nSo is telling that person they're not going to find rep because that press is bad. Which, as it turned out, was a lie.",

"text": "if I hadn't taken Entangled's offer, I never would've debuted. I would've given up on being published, because, WHY BOTHER.\nAnd need I remind you, I spent almost a full year querying this book to agents. No one would take me.",

"text": "\"you only debut once\" is a terribly overrated sentence.\nliterally, who cares if you debut with a smaller press? Who cares if you don't start with a splashy deal at a big 5? \nElitists, that's who.",

"text": "You know what sucks about the Ashley/JP breakup? Every entertainment show will be talking about it tmrw, tabloids posting anonymous quotes and \u201csources are telling us\u201d stories about why the breakup happened.  They don\u2019t need that. Do better. I beg you.",

"text": "Days like today should serve to remind everyone that people get elected to Congress because they are literally incapable of holding any other job.",

"text": "I haven't heard back from any of my pending agent queries since September 20 and while I know this is a long game and a terrible year, I am also dyinnnnnnnng",

"text": "So I see the talkers are out there on “conservative court-packing” so I’ll make it really simple:

Filling vacancies is not court-packing. Not filling vacancies is not court-packing.

Both have a political recourse. Win elections. 

Adding seats IS court-packing. That’s it.",

"text": "If I see a super buff actor playing a regular everyday person in a movie/TV show, and the content does not show the person spending hours in the gym everyday to maintain that physique: just picture me giving you serious side-eye for setting unrealistic body types. Men AND women.",

"text": "I just spent the last 2 hours helping PA voters turn in ballots at an early voting location. The crowd was constant and overwhelming Blue. And I turned my ballot in too! https://t.co/DDLUgsuapA",

"text": "I live and love to help! I'm not at all an expert just want to be a non-judgmental helping hand! We all have a story inside that needs to be shared so let it rip!! Keep going! Defeat does not exist. Keep brainstorming and follow your ideas! 6/6",

"text": "do! Keep going, keep writing, keep querying, and in the words of one of my favorite villains: DEFEAT, does not exist in this dojo, does it? - Well in this writing field but you get the picture! If you ever need a second pair of eyes, advice, words of encouragement, DM me, 5/6",

"text": "it but basically, what I want everyone to gain from my story is DO NOT GIVE UP and to follow your crazy ass ideas! There is somebody out there who you just haven't found yet who loves your characters and your ideas and want to share them to the world just as much as you 4/6",

"text": "I want to tell you all my journey because I think it's pretty crazy but I do not ever want it to come across as I'm boasting or showboating or anything like that! I may write it down in a blog post or something one day or if anybody ever wants to hear it, I'll gladly share 3/6",

"text": "There is a whole world with an audience of people waiting to read your book. Your book will become somebody's favorite story tell, REPEATEDLY! The amount of no's does not matter, I know we're all sick of hearing it but all it takes is one YES to change everything! 2/6",

"text": "This is just a quick thread and friendly reminder to all writers: KEEP GOING! If you feel like you want to stop, don't. If you feel like you're never going to succeed, you will. If you feel like you're story is crazy, nobody's going to understand it or like it, you're wrong. 1/6",
"text": "Parents. At their boy's Beatification.\n\ud83d\ude2d\ud83d\ude2d\ud83d\ude2d",

"text": "@aan__ Ditanya kabar sama kerjaan aja langsung mikir ntar menu katering nikahan pake zuppa soup apa nggak ya",
"text": "@aan__ Diantar pulang kerumah (krn emang searah) aja udh pada nanya ibu-ibu tetangga nanti pas jadi panitia nikahan mau dikasi jilbab syar'i atau baju daster.",

"text": "Kalau kau bs mkn gorengan haram, pigilah ke Jl Yose Rizal, ada popiah legendaris situ. Popiah itu semacam lumpia, isi selada, lobak putih, wortel, bawang goreng, chasio, kepiting. Ada saos cocolannya yg juga bikin rasanya makin nyess. Ini hasil rekomendasi org krn aku gak mkn B2",

"text": "Nggak lengkaplah ke Medan tanpa makan mie sop kampunb. Mie sop itu kyk bakso, tapi alih2 pake bakso, ini pake ayam suir + pilihan gorengan (biasanya risol crispy digunting2 + sate kerang + kerupuk merah putih. Yg plg enak walau tempatnya di atas got: mie sop kampung Jl Bambu.",

"text": "Kelen penggemar sandwich? Buka abis Maghrib di Jl Setiabudi dpn RM ACC seberang Komp Tasbi, ada Roti Jhon: rotinya memanjang dibakar dgn mentega & dilapisi telur, lalu isinya ada pilihan adonan ayam, sapi, atau seafood, lengkap dgn saus & mayones. Instant guilty pleasure! https://t.co/1HLxla8feG",

"text": "Sate padang yg enak di Medan banyak ya, tapi seleraku, temen2ku, sampe mamaku yg buka puasa aja pake ini: sate padang Agustiar Amir di Jl S Parman, di sudut sblm belok Jl Karo (tempat Macehat). Ada ayam, daging, usus dll, lengkap dgn kerupuk jangek. Buka jam 1, jam 4 abes.",

"text": "Utk sarapan juga ada 1 tempat yg diserbu banyak org: bihun bebek Asie di Jl Kumango. Aku nggak mkn bebek, tp testimoni temanku kuah kaldunya gurih seger, potongan bebeknya empuk & banyak, taburan bawang putihnya bikin makin sempurna.",

"text": "Nasi uduk & lontong itu yg plg enak justru yg jualan malem, istilahnya lontong malam. Ini keterlaluan enaknya: lontong mlm Bu Sari di Jl Medan Area Selatan. Nasi uduknya enaknya yaampuuun! Kami sekeluarga sering beli buat makan malam. Cat: hari Minggu nggak jualan. https://t.co/oI3jAMOIDl",

"text": "Kelen suka nyemil martabak Bangka? Sore2 di Jl Gajahmada berderet yg jual, tapi favoritku & kawan2ku adalah martabak Abang Kakak (yg tendanya biru), bs pake ayam, daging, ukuran biasa sampe jumbo. Crispy di luar, gurih di dlm, murah pulak!",

"text": "Utk makan siang ada tambahan pilihan: nasi ikan sombom (ikan acar) + telur dadar Kak Yus di dekat rel kereta Jl Pandu. Ini warung bgt ya, panas gilak, rame gilak jg krn makanannya enak kali & lbh enak mkn di tempat drpd bungkus. Arrive early: sblm jam 11.30 atau siap ngantri.",

"text": "Kalau di nasi uduk Tom & Jerry, walau rebutannya kyk serbuan zombie, ada nomor antrian jadi jelas kita dipanggil berdasarkan urutan dateng. Di tenda biru berdasarkan seberapa gencar kau \u2018teror\u2019 yg bungkus2nya \ud83e\udd23\ud83e\udd23",

"text": "Utk oleh2, baru teringat buat kalian yg makan haram: 7. Bakpia Tamiang di Jl Tamiang, isinya macem2 dari kacang ijo sampe abon B2. Aku tau tempat ini juga krn nemenin kawanku yg mau bawa berkotak2 utk keluarganya. Ada tester, kawanku lgs blg: \u201cJgn mkn ya, Ka, haram tu.\u201d",

"text": "coba yg ayam goreng gumarang atau uni emi tadi lah. atau kalo mau yg dgn nasi, skip ayam penyet ria atau surabaya, kau ke resto semanggi di ruko centrepoint, pesan nasi daun jeruk (komplit udh pake ayam goreng berpotong2, cumi2an, sambel kentang dll) bisa buat makan bertiga. https://t.co/7t1PKM9KhW",

"text": "kyk mamak bapakku lbh suka tip top drpd bakery yg \u2018masa kini\u2019 krn katanya rasanya klasik, pas, nggak terlalu \u2018lemak\u2019 gak flat jg. ternyata kawan2 yg muda pun dibawain ini suka. ada 2 bakery klasik di medan: tip top & toko langsung di jl pandu (aku ga tau yg ini msh \u2018idup\u2019 ga) https://t.co/C7KzbotiIq",

"text": "Sekian dulu rekomendasi dariku. Tentu msh banyak yg tak tersebut awak, spti bihun bebek Asie Jl Kumango, nasi ikan gembung acar + telur dadar terenak sedunia di warung Kak Yus, sampe Martabak Gapa. Banyak kali pun! Selamat datang di Medan, tempat kita berkawan krn makanan!",

"text": "4. Oleh2 yg jrg diketahui org pdhl sekali dikasih itu siapapun yg dikasih pasti nagih: berbagai jenis cake di Tip Top, Jl A Yani. Mau mocca ceres, chocolate, blackforest, dll dsb, bs beli per potong campur2 tarokkan dlm 1 box. Krn handcarry, jgn tergoda pula kau makan di bandara",

"text": "1. Let's start with the obvious: bolu Meranti, ada di Jl Kruing dan Jl Sisingamangaraja. Mau keju, moka, coklat dll dst enak semuanya itu.\n2. Di Jl Kruing juga ada sate kerang Rahmat, ini kalo dikulkasin juga kawan2ku masih bisa pada makan sampe 3 hari (dipanaskanlah).",

"text": "Utk yg makan haram, malem2 itu paling enak ke kawasan Jl Selat Panjang/Jl Semarang, khususnya ke Bakmi Tiongsim. Aku udh bbrp kali bawa temen ke sini enak kali pun katanya. Penjual kwetiaw goreng dll jg banyak di sepanjang jln ini, tp fokus ke Tiongsim udah.",

"text": "Kerang rebus di Medan dihidangkan masih dalam kulitnya, tinggal dibuka, dicocol ke saus tadi, WUIIIIH, langsung lupa semua masalah hidup tu. Tapi jangan lupa kolesterolmu yaa, nanti nggak sadar udah abis pulak 20 biji \ud83e\udd23\ud83e\udd23\ud83e\udd23\ud83e\udd23",

"text": "Masok kita ke menu jelang midnite, sambil nongkrong2 bodo membahas hidup atau bola atau apalah suka ati. Makan kerang rebus kita? Ada di Simpang Limun. Khasnya kerang rebus Medan itu: kerangnya besar2 seger dari Tj Balai, trus sambelnya campuran cabe, saus nanas, sambal kacang",

"text": "Mau mie-miean? Panggil grab/gojek, cabut ke mie aceh Titi Bobrok di Jl Setiabudi. Mie-nya semacam mie kuning gitu tapi warna lbh keoranyean, digoreng becek dgn bumbu rempah khas Aceh, pedes2 nagih. Catatan: tempatnya rame kali ya.",

"text": "Pengen ayam goreng yg terenak sedunia juga selain ayam goreng di Uni Emi tadi? Meluncur kelen ke RM Gumarang Jaya di Jl Brigjend Katamso, minta ayam goreng yg baru dari kuali jd panas2 gurih menggetarkan lidah! Menu tambahan silakan pilih, kyk di rumah makan Padang lah.",

"text": "Oke lanjut ke makan malam kita? Pilihan pertama tempat yg murah, meriah, enak: seafood Wajir di Jl Wajir. Segala macam seafood-nya sampe menu non seafood kyk ayam cabe ijonya ENAK GILAK! Pesan jg tahu jepang goreng tepung deh, udh cuma goceng, enak pulak, suka aku.",

"text": "Akong Acim ini bukanya sampe larut malam sih, jadi kalo malas sore2 ke situ (krn tempatnya panas dan udara Medan emang panas pula, walau aku sih seringnya ke sini sore2 pulang kerja), bisa malem2. Makin malem makin rame. Menu minuman khas: jeruk peras dingin dan soda cap Badak",

"text": "Cuma mau nyemil2 lucu? Bisa meluncur ke gerai kue Tivoli di supermarket Brastagi Tiara Jl. Cut Mutia, di situ ada kue roti jala gulung isinya kari kentang, yaampuuun aku sih bisa abis 4 sendiri ya.",

"text": "6. Utk penikmat makanan haram, ada kwetiaw yg kata kawanku enak kali pun, lengkap dgn berbagai potongan B2 dll ntahapahapa aku pun tak paham cuma pernah nganterin, yaitu kwetiaw Ateng di Jl. S. Parman. Kwetiaw-nya kwetiaw beras jd kering, & kata kawanku enaknya kurang ajaar.",

"text": "4. Nggak mungkinlah ke Medan tanpa makan soto Medan kan? Yg bedain soto Medan itu dari tempat lain ada di rempahnya, kuahnya kental bersantan dan warna cenderung kehijauan. Meluncur ke Soto Kesawan seberang Tjong A Fie, mau soto ayam, daging suka ati tp yg plg spesial udang.",

"text": "3. Ingin nasi Padang yg betolan nendang rasanya? Meluncur ke RM Uni Emi di daerah Petisah (any grab/gojek driver would know), pesan nasi kapau komplit. Catatan: ayam goreng pop-nya jg salah satu yg terenak di dunia (biarin lebai \ud83e\udd23\ud83e\udd23).",

"text": "Pilihan makan siang di Medan itu endless! Bbrp yg menurutku hrs kelen coba:\n1. Nelayan. Skip all the main menu (krn kalo nasgor/migor-nya nggak istimewa), menu wajib itu justru dimsum2an, lee hong kien (stik udang dibalur mayones), dan chong fen 2 musim (INI WAJIB!)",

"text": "Krn sarapan udh berat, nggak ada brunch2an sih di Medan, tapi kalau mau coba menu brunch yg enak (ini nggak khas Medan tapi aku blm nemu dmn pun yg seenak ini), bisa coba brioche french toast di Thirty-Six Jl Multatuli. It's heaven on a plate. Heaven.",

"text": "Kita masuk nasi uduk yaa. \n1. Nasi uduk Tom & Jerry di Jl Surabaya. Ini. Enak. Banget. Porsi nggak banyak, lauknya yg berlimpah mulai dr tauco, telur, & yg membedakan dia dr tempat nasi uduk lain adalah dia pake sambel terasi Medan. Nendang! PS: ngantrinya mayaan.",

"text": "2. Lontong Mongonsidi, letaknya di Jl Mongonsidi (ada satu tenda gitu nggak jauh dari seberang KFC Walikota). Pesan lengkap ya: lontong + telor + sate kerang. Bakwannya jg segede gaban dan ENAK!! Guilty pleasure bgt.",

"text": "So no, it\u2019s not avocado toast (who does this?) and lattes that\u2019s keeping people from supporting themselves. It\u2019s hard to pull yourself up by the bootstraps when you can\u2019t afford them, or food, because you\u2019re working 188 hrs/wk for shelter and school. *steps off soapbox* 8/8",

"text": "The billionaire class of America, 614 people, increased their net wealth by nearly $1 TRILLION THIS YEAR. They could collective send every man, woman, and child in this country a $3000 check and still be the billionaires they were last year. 7/8",

"text": "The livable wage in this country is a systematic problem involving lots of factors. A big one of which is, and always has been, greed. People at the top want more $$ and offload the cost to the employees and consumers. 6/8",

"text": "EVERY job is important/needed, or we wouldn\u2019t have it. If people can\u2019t survive on a job, and they all collectively decided to \u201cfind a better job\u201d, then you can fix your car yourself, make your own lattes, and clean your own office. Don\u2019t see anyone volunteering for that. 5/8",

"text": "But Sean that\u2019ll make their salary nearly as much as mine! So? You\u2019re not better than them. Try a little compassion and understanding for your neighbor. Your happiness/satisfaction shouldn\u2019t depend on being the highest earner on the block. 4/8",

"text": "And how can they get a better job when they can\u2019t afford to buy food, let alone pay for college? College on average is $25k a year, so 66 hrs a week to pay for that. Keeping track that\u2019s 118 hrs a week for room school. Still not eating anything. 3/8",

"text": "If your argument is that prices will go up, they already have and wages haven\u2019t gone with them. If your argument is that people should work better jobs, who do you think is going to serve you that food or check you out at the grocery store then? Your want demands those jobs. 2/8",

"text": "Lots of talk about #MinimumWage being $15. Let\u2019s go for a walk here. Fun fact, average US rent is roughly $1500 /mo. That\u2019s a 52 work week at $7.25 /hr JUST TO PAY RENT. 2 gal of milk or 6 gal of gas is an hrs worth of work. 1/8",

"text": "*phone rings*

National Weather Service

“What’s the low temp tonight”

I tell him.

“I knew the station would be wrong. Do you why I know that? They hired a bunch of Democrats”

I don’t say anything 

“Did you here me?”

Yes.

Oh ok.
